[[File:Pylat1.jpg|250px|thumb|A Neimoidian bird cage containing a pylat bird]]
'''Neimoidian bird cages''' were small devices used for holding avians such as the [[Pylat bird/Legends|pylat bird]]. These cages were fitted with force field generators built in to confine the bird.<ref name="SWCVD">''[[Star Wars: The Complete Visual Dictionary]]''</ref> A thin perch rose from a pole in the center of the cage's base.

The [[Neimoidian/Legends|Neimoidian]] [[Nute Gunray/Legends|Nute Gunray]] received a red-spotted pylat bird as an anonymous gift, and he kept it on display in a Neimoidian bird cage in his office, with it quickly becoming the envy of his peers. [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious]] revealed that he sent Gunray the bird and threated to Force choke it in its cage after he unexpectedly contacted Gunray for the first time, forcing Gunray to enter into a reluctant alliance with the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]].<ref name="Darth Plagueis">[[Darth Plagueis (novel)|''Darth Plagueis'']]</ref>

These cages were also found aboard [[Lucrehulk-class battleship/Legends|''Lucrehulk''-class battleships]] such as [[Saak'ak/Legends|''Saak'ak'']] during the [[Invasion of Naboo/Legends|Invasion of Naboo]].

